  "prompt": "In the history of the modern Olympics, have there been more gold medals or silver medals given out?",
  "response": "In the history of the modern Olympics, there have generally been more gold medals awarded than silver medals. This is due to the nature of how medals are allocated in multi-event sports. Each event typically awards one gold medal to the winner. In many cases, there are also team events where multiple gold medals can be awarded for a single event, resulting in a higher overall count of gold medals compared to silver. \n\nHowever, the total number of medals awarded in any specific Olympics can vary based on the number of sports, events, and formats used in that edition of the Games. Nonetheless, across the entirety of Olympic history, gold medals tend to outnumber silver medals. For the most current statistics, checking the latest data from the International Olympic Committee would provide the most accurate figures.",
